function BlogPage() {
  return (
    <>
      <div className="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-10">
        <header className="mb-8">
          <h1 className="text-3xl font-bold leading-tight">
            What Is the Difference Between Interior and Exterior Waterproofing Services
          </h1>
          <p className="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600">June 5, 2025</p>
          <nav className="mt-1 text-xs text-gray-500">
            Home » Blogs » What Is the Difference Between Interior and Exterior Waterproofing Services
          </nav>
        </header>

        <article className="prose max-w-none">
          <p>
            When it comes to protecting your property from water damage, understanding the key differences between interior and exterior waterproofing is essential. Both methods help prevent water intrusion, but they work in different ways and are best for different scenarios. At Waterproofed, we design and install both—with solutions that last.
          </p>

          <h2 className="mt-10 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Understanding Waterproofing: Why It Matters</h2>
          <p>
            Unchecked moisture can lead to mold growth, foundation damage, warped flooring, and even electrical hazards. Waterproofing is not one-size-fits-all; systems are tailored to where and how water is entering the structure.
          </p>
          <ul className="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Protects structural integrity (basements, crawl spaces, foundations)</li>
            <li>Prevents health risks from mold and mildew</li>
            <li>Preserves finishes and reduces long‑term repair costs</li>
          </ul>


          <h2 className="mt-10 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Interior Waterproofing: A Reactive Yet Effective Solution</h2>
          <p>
            Interior methods manage water that has already penetrated walls or slabs. They are budget‑friendly, less disruptive, and ideal for addressing existing intrusion quickly.
          </p>
          <p className="font-semibold">Key features:</p>
          <ul className="list-disc pl-6">
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Drainage systems:</span> Perimeter trench and perforated piping beneath the slab re‑route water.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Sump pumps:</span> Collect and discharge water safely away from the home.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Vapor barriers:</span> Reduce humidity transfer through interior walls.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Sealants/epoxy injections:</span> Treat minor cracks and seepage paths.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 className="mt-10 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Exterior Waterproofing: A Proactive Defense</h2>
          <p>
            Exterior systems stop water before it reaches the structure. They are comprehensive and labor‑intensive, offering the most complete long‑term protection.
          </p>
          <p className="font-semibold">Key components:</p>
          <ul className="list-disc pl-6">
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Excavation:</span> Down to the footings for full access to the foundation walls.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Membranes & sealants:</span> Robust coatings/membranes that block infiltration.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Drainage boards:</span> Protect membranes and channel water down.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">French drains:</span> Carry water away to reduce hydrostatic pressure.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 className="mt-10 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Common Waterproofing Issues Homeowners Face</h2>
          <ul className="list-disc pl-6">
            <li>Basement flooding after heavy rain</li>
            <li>Foundation wall cracks or bowing</li>
            <li>Mold and mildew odors in lower levels</li>
            <li>Peeling paint or efflorescence on walls</li>
            <li>Persistent dampness or puddles</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 className="mt-10 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Interior vs. Exterior Waterproofing: Key Differences</h2>
          <ul className="list-disc pl-6">
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Purpose:</span> Interior manages water after entry; exterior prevents entry.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Cost:</span> Interior is generally lower; exterior is a higher upfront investment.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Installation:</span> Interior is less invasive; exterior requires excavation.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Time:</span> Interior often 1–3 days; exterior up to a week or more.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Longevity:</span> Interior is medium‑term; exterior offers long‑term protection.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Best for:</span> Interior—existing water issues; Exterior—new builds or full protection.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 className="mt-10 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Why Choose Waterproofed?</h2>
          <ul className="list-disc pl-6">
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Expert diagnosis:</span> We identify root causes before proposing solutions.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Comprehensive services:</span> From minor fixes to full exterior systems.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Skilled technicians:</span> Trained in the latest technologies and techniques.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Guaranteed results:</span> Warranties on materials and labor.</li>
            <li><span className="font-semibold">Flexible financing:</span> Options to fit most budgets.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 className="mt-10 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Final Thoughts</h2>
          <p>
            Interior systems provide quick relief for existing problems, while exterior methods offer long‑term, preventive protection. The right approach depends on your property, soil conditions, foundation type, and budget. With Waterproofed, you do not have to decide alone—we guide you to the best solution and stand behind our work.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
      <Testimonial />
